632
01:00:17,330 --> 01:00:21,279
She's going to have the enemy
ghost way. We leave this afternoon.

633
01:00:21,501 --> 01:00:25,450
- Wh... Where's the ceremony?
- It’s at her clan's village.

634
01:00:25,671 --> 01:00:27,628
- Old Woman Butte.
- You're gonna take her away?

635
01:00:27,840 --> 01:00:32,217
- This girl needs a doctor.
- She's already seen a doctor.

636
01:00:36,348 --> 01:00:41,473
Chinamen's heads? Chosin? I’ve never
heard her talk that way before.

637
01:00:42,021 --> 01:00:43,812
Is someone teaching that
to your kids in class?

638
01:00:44,023 --> 01:00:47,107
Yeah, sure.
Right next to Jack and Jill.

639
01:00:48,485 --> 01:00:51,688
Colonel Hawthorne was at Chosin.
Did she talk to him?

640
01:00:51,905 --> 01:00:54,657
She had no contact with him.
He hated children.

641
01:00:56,618 --> 01:01:01,245
This isn't just about some drunk who
burned himself up at the school, is it?

642
01:01:03,333 --> 01:01:05,242
Can you tell me the truth, Thomas?

643
01:01:07,379 --> 01:01:09,418
Did you ever read
the Bible, Katherine?

644
01:01:10,006 --> 01:01:11,666
Long time ago.

645
01:01:12,425 --> 01:01:17,134
Ever notice how in the Bible, whenever
God needed to punish someone

646
01:01:17,347 --> 01:01:19,304
or make an example,

647
01:01:19,516 --> 01:01:24,224
or whenever God needed a killing,
He sent an angel?

648
01:01:25,646 --> 01:01:29,561
Did you ever wonder what
a creature like that must be like?

649
01:01:30,443 --> 01:01:32,435
A whole existence spent
praising your God,

650
01:01:32,653 --> 01:01:34,895
but always with one wing
dipped in blood.

651
01:01:36,324 --> 01:01:40,985
Would you ever really
want to see an angel?

652
01:01:41,996 --> 01:01:45,162
- Why are you asking me this?
- They want Colonel Hawthorne.

653
01:01:46,834 --> 01:01:50,285
They want a dead,
forgotten, psychotic colonel.

654
01:01:50,713 --> 01:01:52,041
They?

655
01:01:57,594 --> 01:02:00,132
There was a man
at my school this morning.

656
01:02:00,347 --> 01:02:03,467
The children were calling him Gabriel.

657
01:02:03,684 --> 01:02:06,175
He had Sandra on his lap.

658
01:02:07,604 --> 01:02:09,976
What does he want with my kids?

659
01:02:10,190 --> 01:02:12,562
I don't know, Katherine.

660
01:02:14,694 --> 01:02:17,066
But I gotta find him.

661
01:02:17,906 --> 01:02:19,898
I know where you can find him.

662
01:02:30,251 --> 01:02:32,208
He was parked right here.

663
01:02:57,069 --> 01:02:58,860
It’s cold.

