747
01:13:25,224 --> 01:13:28,427
- Not yet. Come back.
- (Gurgling Continues)

748
01:13:30,312 --> 01:13:32,388
- Come on, back it up.
- (Gasping)

749
01:13:32,606 --> 01:13:36,189
- That's it. Come on back.
- (Coughs)

750
01:13:36,402 --> 01:13:40,482
Ooh. Ahh.
(Coughing Continues)

751
01:13:46,870 --> 01:13:50,073
- Hi!
- No, no, no, no, no.

752
01:13:50,582 --> 01:13:52,041
Shh.

753
01:13:54,086 --> 01:13:56,458
Don't start. I hate that.

754
01:13:57,297 --> 01:13:59,420
Come on, don't start.

755
01:13:59,633 --> 01:14:01,506
It’s only for a short time.

756
01:14:02,385 --> 01:14:04,010
Promise.

757
01:14:07,474 --> 01:14:08,802
(People Singing, Chanting)

758
01:14:39,046 --> 01:14:40,754
(Whispering)
Hello, Katherine.

759
01:14:44,426 --> 01:14:45,755
We must talk.

760
01:14:47,554 --> 01:14:51,552
- Oh, my God.
- God? God is love.

761
01:14:54,603 --> 01:14:56,263
I don't love you.

762
01:14:57,356 --> 01:14:59,348
I... I can't. I can't do this.

763
01:14:59,566 --> 01:15:03,778
I can lay you out and fill your mouth
with your mother's faeces.

764
01:15:04,488 --> 01:15:06,065
Or we can talk.

765
01:15:17,292 --> 01:15:18,786
(Growls)

766
01:15:19,335 --> 01:15:20,664
(Roars)

767
01:15:26,634 --> 01:15:29,386
- Are you one of them?
- Them?

768
01:15:30,930 --> 01:15:32,341
Are you an angel?

769
01:15:32,557 --> 01:15:37,633
(Chuckles) I am the first angel,
loved once above all others.

770
01:15:37,853 --> 01:15:40,095
A perfect love.

771
01:15:40,314 --> 01:15:43,315
# But like all true love #

772
01:15:43,526 --> 01:15:48,069
# One day it
withered on the vine ##

773
01:15:48,781 --> 01:15:50,608
(inhales)

774
01:15:52,034 --> 01:15:55,734
Ahh, the winged
party boy is about.

775
01:15:57,706 --> 01:16:00,909
Come to feed on the guts
of your little Mary.

776
01:16:01,126 --> 01:16:03,582
- Are you a part of it?
- No, Katherine.

777
01:16:03,795 --> 01:16:07,496
Other angels have made this war
because they hate you.

778
01:16:07,716 --> 01:16:10,207
You and all humans.

779
01:16:10,427 --> 01:16:15,504
God has put you in His grace and
pushed them aside. They're desperate.

780
01:16:16,391 --> 01:16:18,964
They've never been able to
conquer the other loyal angels.

781
01:16:19,185 --> 01:16:22,768
And so this war has remained
in stalemate for thousands of years.

782
01:16:23,315 --> 01:16:29,400
And while this state of affairs endures,
no soul can meet its God.

783
01:16:29,612 --> 01:16:33,147
Your parents and their parents
and so on, from the beginning,

784
01:16:33,366 --> 01:16:35,655
lie still in wormy earth.

785
01:16:35,868 --> 01:16:38,739
Of course, some of them
do come to me eventually.

786
01:16:38,955 --> 01:16:43,830
For while Heaven may be closed,
I am always open, even on Christmas.

787
01:16:50,299 --> 01:16:52,007
Gabriel has a plan.

788
01:16:52,760 --> 01:16:57,754
Humans... and how I love
you talking monkeys for this...

789
01:16:57,973 --> 01:17:03,015
know more about war and treachery
of the spirit than any angel.

790
01:17:03,771 --> 01:17:06,143
Gabriel is well aware of this

791
01:17:06,357 --> 01:17:11,102
and has found a way to steal the
blackest soul on Earth to fight for him.

792
01:17:11,320 --> 01:17:14,902
If he wins, Heaven opens.

793
01:17:18,994 --> 01:17:21,699
I know that this new Heaven
will just be another Hell.

794
01:17:23,040 --> 01:17:25,827
You see, I’m not here
to help you and the little bitch

795
01:17:26,042 --> 01:17:27,834
because I love you
or because I care for you,

796
01:17:28,044 --> 01:17:30,535
but because two Hells
is one Hell too many

797
01:17:30,755 --> 01:17:32,415
and I can't have that.

798
01:17:33,842 --> 01:17:38,302
What I’m offering you is a chance
not only to save Mary,

799
01:17:38,513 --> 01:17:42,463
but to finally open
Heaven to your kind.

800
01:17:43,851 --> 01:17:45,761
What do you say?

801
01:17:49,148 --> 01:17:51,057
(Crickets Chirping)

802
01:18:02,787 --> 01:18:05,574
I saw the devil tonight.

803
01:18:16,467 --> 01:18:18,922
If you have something to say...

804
01:18:21,638 --> 01:18:23,880
why can't you say it to me?

805
01:18:29,688 --> 01:18:31,016
Thomas.

806
01:18:39,197 --> 01:18:41,984
I had a voice once, Katherine.

807
01:18:45,203 --> 01:18:47,694
For as long as I could remember,

808
01:18:47,914 --> 01:18:54,035
I had a voice that called me to my
God, that called me to church.

809
01:18:54,712 --> 01:18:57,832
And on the day that I needed
that voice the most,

810
01:19:00,551 --> 01:19:02,259
it left me.

811
01:19:03,846 --> 01:19:07,013
It’s better never
having known that voice.

812
01:19:09,977 --> 01:19:15,316
All I know is that I’m not going to let
anything happen to Mary. All right?

813
01:19:40,215 --> 01:19:44,877
Say, ma'am, any idea where
I can find Old Woman Butte?

814
01:19:45,095 --> 01:19:46,755
Yeah, it's on the reservation.

815
01:19:47,222 --> 01:19:50,638
Don't suppose you could be
just a tad more specific,

816
01:19:50,850 --> 01:19:52,594
Madge?

817
01:19:55,105 --> 01:19:59,185
The light. It was so...

818
01:19:59,901 --> 01:20:02,226
br... bright.

819
01:20:04,447 --> 01:20:07,020
- Isn't your friend hungry?
- What?

820
01:20:08,451 --> 01:20:11,701
Not for a while, I’m afraid.
Funniest thing.

821
01:20:13,831 --> 01:20:15,373
Don't do that.

822
01:20:15,583 --> 01:20:17,991
Take the 522
to the Sonsela Wash cutoff.

823
01:20:18,211 --> 01:20:21,414
- Right.
- First dirt road, go left 20, 25 miles.

824
01:20:21,631 --> 01:20:23,956
- You'll see it.
- Much obliged.

825
01:20:24,175 --> 01:20:27,129
- Let's get crackin', Rachael.
- No!

826
01:20:30,055 --> 01:20:37,221
Eternity here. In that sagging skin suit.
Or one more day with me.

827
01:20:38,313 --> 01:20:43,770
- Why?
- Can't drive. But I can wait.

828
01:20:45,237 --> 01:20:49,317
Until the stars burn out,
if you don't make up your mind.

829
01:20:55,872 --> 01:20:58,244
- I doubt we'll meet again.
- Suits me.

830
01:20:58,458 --> 01:21:00,367
Thank Heaven.

831
01:21:18,061 --> 01:21:20,219
Little Tommy Dagget.

832
01:21:20,438 --> 01:21:24,601
How I loved listening
to your sweet prayers every night.

833
01:21:24,817 --> 01:21:30,855
And then you'd jump in your bed,
so afraid I was under there. And I was.

834
01:21:34,702 --> 01:21:37,572
Do you know what Hell
really is, Thomas?

835
01:21:37,788 --> 01:21:41,074
It’s not lakes of burning oil
or chains of ice.

836
01:21:41,292 --> 01:21:43,747
It’s being removed from God's sight,

837
01:21:43,961 --> 01:21:46,286
having His Word taken from you.

838
01:21:46,505 --> 01:21:51,879
- (Panting)
- It’s hard to believe. So hard.

839
01:21:53,178 --> 01:21:56,179
I know that better than anyone.

840
01:21:56,390 --> 01:21:58,881
And there's your weapon.

841
01:22:00,978 --> 01:22:04,228
Think, Thomas, think.

842
01:22:04,439 --> 01:22:07,310
What is the one thing
essential to an angel,

843
01:22:07,526 --> 01:22:10,610
the thing that holds
his entire being together?

844
01:22:10,820 --> 01:22:12,778
Faith. Faith, faith.

845
01:22:12,989 --> 01:22:16,192
And what would happen
if that faith was tested,

846
01:22:16,409 --> 01:22:22,245
and an angel, just like you,
didn't understand?

847
01:22:24,667 --> 01:22:26,790
Use that.

848
01:22:27,295 --> 01:22:29,169
Use it!

849
01:23:31,191 --> 01:23:33,479
He's coming.

850
01:23:40,241 --> 01:23:42,364
(Chanting)

851
01:24:00,511 --> 01:24:03,512
Go inside, lock the door.

852
01:24:03,764 --> 01:24:07,513
There's one shot. OK?

853
01:24:13,148 --> 01:24:15,105
It’ll be OK.

854
01:24:41,384 --> 01:24:45,334
You're gonna love it, Rachael.
It’ll be our night to howl.

855
01:24:58,109 --> 01:25:00,860
Nice move. Beautifully done.

856
01:25:01,070 --> 01:25:03,478
Tommy, you've got to
come work for me.

857
01:25:03,698 --> 01:25:06,615
Upstairs.
I... I could get you in now.

858
01:25:06,826 --> 01:25:09,447
You'll love it.
Nobody tells you when to go to bed.

859
01:25:09,662 --> 01:25:11,738
You eat all the ice cream you want.

860
01:25:11,956 --> 01:25:17,163
You get to kill all day,
all night, just like an angel!

861
01:25:17,378 --> 01:25:20,082
Save yourself, friend!

862
01:25:20,297 --> 01:25:24,046
Why go to the wall
for that bitch and her rug rat?

863
01:25:24,259 --> 01:25:26,584
It all turns out the same
anyway. Now, later.

864
01:25:26,803 --> 01:25:29,010
I’m gonna rip that kid apart.

865
01:25:29,222 --> 01:25:32,638
I’m not an angel! I’m just a man.

866
01:25:32,851 --> 01:25:36,101
Which means I got something
you don't. It’s a soul.

867
01:25:40,275 --> 01:25:41,603
This is gonna really hurt.

868
01:25:42,235 --> 01:25:43,610
Your war...

869
01:25:44,571 --> 01:25:46,777
- Make it good.
- Your war is a lie!

870
01:25:47,949 --> 01:25:51,400
- Right.
- It’s not about humans. It’s about God.

871
01:25:51,619 --> 01:25:53,493
What do you know
about that, you monkey?

872
01:25:53,705 --> 01:25:56,540
I don't have to, Gabriel.
I know you.

873
01:25:56,749 --> 01:26:00,367
I know what it's like
to be ignored, pushed aside.

874
01:26:00,586 --> 01:26:02,793
I know your anger, Gabriel.

875
01:26:03,297 --> 01:26:07,509
I know what it's like
to lose your faith in the Word. I know.

876
01:26:08,427 --> 01:26:12,092
'Cause you hate Him.
You hate Him just a little bit.

877
01:26:12,848 --> 01:26:14,924
'Cause you're jealous.

878
01:26:15,476 --> 01:26:18,596
That's what this war's about...
jealousy.

879
01:26:19,271 --> 01:26:22,854
Jealousy that He could love
something more than you.

880
01:26:23,275 --> 01:26:25,766
Something with a soul.

881
01:26:27,655 --> 01:26:29,446
Well.

882
01:26:29,656 --> 01:26:34,365
If you wanted to prove
your side was right, Gabriel, so badly,

883
01:26:35,037 --> 01:26:37,160
why didn't you just ask Him?

884
01:26:37,372 --> 01:26:38,914
Why didn't you just ask God?

885
01:26:43,003 --> 01:26:44,497
Because...

886
01:26:46,173 --> 01:26:49,339
He doesn't talk to me any more.

887
01:27:05,400 --> 01:27:06,728
(Sniffing)

888
01:27:07,151 --> 01:27:08,480
(Chanting)

889
01:27:17,161 --> 01:27:19,118
Gabriel!

890
01:27:33,385 --> 01:27:35,841
- I’m getting so fed up with you.
- Go to hell.

891
01:27:36,055 --> 01:27:39,340
Heaven, darling, Heaven.
At least get the zip code right.

892
01:27:39,558 --> 01:27:43,390
- It’s all the same to you, isn't it?
- No. In Heaven, we believe in love.

893
01:27:43,937 --> 01:27:47,223
- What do you love, Gabriel?
- Cracking your skull.

894
01:27:47,441 --> 01:27:49,766
(Grunting)

895
01:27:49,985 --> 01:27:52,855
- (Thomas Screaming)
- Kill me!

896
01:27:53,071 --> 01:27:54,980
(Grunting)

897
01:28:03,873 --> 01:28:06,364
Oh, God!
(Grunting)

898
01:28:09,629 --> 01:28:11,669
Mary!

899
01:28:19,597 --> 01:28:21,756
- Go home.
- (Growls)

900
01:28:23,309 --> 01:28:25,052
Go home!

901
01:28:33,986 --> 01:28:38,399
(Speaking In Dialect)

902
01:28:38,616 --> 01:28:40,489
Finish it.

903
01:28:42,536 --> 01:28:43,995
(Growling)

904
01:28:44,830 --> 01:28:47,036
(Chanting Resumes)

905
01:28:48,208 --> 01:28:49,619
Long time.

906
01:28:50,085 --> 01:28:51,745
This war is mine.

907
01:28:51,962 --> 01:28:56,173
Your war is arrogance.
That makes it evil.

908
01:28:57,176 --> 01:28:58,835
That's mine.

909
01:28:59,553 --> 01:29:03,337
Lucifer, sitting in your basement,

910
01:29:03,557 --> 01:29:06,178
sulking over your
breakup with the boss.

911
01:29:07,185 --> 01:29:09,474
You're nothing.

912
01:29:11,314 --> 01:29:13,223
Time to come home, Gabriel.

913
01:29:13,441 --> 01:29:14,817
(Grunts)

914
01:29:31,751 --> 01:29:34,040
(Coughing)

915
01:29:36,464 --> 01:29:37,792
(Thunder Rumbling)

916
01:29:46,223 --> 01:29:48,797
(Coughing Continues)

917
01:29:54,064 --> 01:29:55,974
(Yells)

918
01:30:48,326 --> 01:30:50,698
The enemy ghost is gone.

919
01:30:53,748 --> 01:30:56,239
(Growling)

920
01:31:00,588 --> 01:31:02,296
(Squeals)

921
01:31:07,177 --> 01:31:08,506
(Hissing)

922
01:31:10,514 --> 01:31:14,097
The war's over. It’s done.

923
01:31:17,896 --> 01:31:21,431
No. I want you both
to come home with me.

924
01:31:21,650 --> 01:31:23,192
Never.

925
01:31:23,402 --> 01:31:25,939
"I love you.
I love you more than Jesus."

926
01:31:27,406 --> 01:31:29,398
You owe me one.

927
01:31:30,909 --> 01:31:33,067
You're gonna ask me
to take you home.

928
01:31:33,703 --> 01:31:35,032
- No.
- You will.

929
01:31:35,246 --> 01:31:38,200
Because anything else will be worse
than you could ever imagine.

930
01:31:38,416 --> 01:31:39,827
Katherine.

931
01:31:47,634 --> 01:31:50,041
I have my soul.

932
01:31:50,261 --> 01:31:52,384
And I have my faith.

933
01:31:55,475 --> 01:31:58,843
What do you have... angel?

934
01:32:04,650 --> 01:32:07,651
Leave the light on, Thomas.

935
01:32:13,200 --> 01:32:15,656
Is he coming back?

936
01:32:18,622 --> 01:32:20,496
I don't think so.

937
01:32:51,696 --> 01:32:55,445
(Thomas) And in the end
I think it must be about faith.

938
01:32:55,658 --> 01:32:59,870
And if faith is a choice,
then it can be lost...

939
01:33:00,079 --> 01:33:02,866
for a man, an angel

940
01:33:03,082 --> 01:33:05,787
or the devil himself.

941
01:33:06,002 --> 01:33:10,414
And if faith means never
completely understanding God's plan,

942
01:33:10,631 --> 01:33:14,546
then maybe understanding
just a part of it, our part,

943
01:33:14,760 --> 01:33:17,298
is what it is to have a soul.

944
01:33:17,513 --> 01:33:23,183
And maybe, in the end,
that's what being human is after all.

